   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Here is a follow-up to #18002, again with the goal of simplifying (potential) BIP341 code.\r\n\r\nInstead of passing a begin and end iterator of the initial stack to `ExecuteWitnessScript`, they are turned into a `Span<const valtype>`, representing a span of `valtype`s in memory. This allows `VerifyWitnessProgram` to operate on that span directly, instead of juggling iterators around (which would be exacerbated by #17977 if trying to avoid copying the stack).",
